Frontend:

HTML/CSS/JavaScript: Responsible for the presentation layer, user interface components, and interactivity.
React/Vue.js: Frontend frameworks for building dynamic single-page applications (SPAs).
Backend:

Python: Backend language for server-side logic and API development.
Flask/Django: Python web frameworks for handling HTTP requests, routing, and business logic.
Database (PostgreSQL): Relational database for storing user data, game progress, resource links, and feedback.
Server:

Hosting: Cloud-based hosting (e.g., AWS EC2, Azure App Service) for deploying the web application.
Web Server: NGINX or Apache for serving web content and handling HTTP requests.
APIs:

RESTful APIs: Used for communication between frontend and backend services.
Authentication: OAuth or JWT for user authentication and authorization.
External Services:

Video Hosting: Integration with video platforms (e.g., YouTube API) for hosting and streaming simulation videos.
Content Delivery Networks (CDNs): For efficient content delivery, especially for videos and static assets.
Security:

HTTPS: Secure communication protocol to protect user data.
Data Encryption: Encrypting sensitive data stored in the database.
User Authentication: OAuth/OpenID for secure login and session management.
Visualization of User Journey
1. Homepage
User Action: User lands on the homepage.
Navigation: Chooses between "Trivia Game," "Simulation," or "Resources."
Goal: Start exploring the selected part of the platform.
2. Cultural Trivia Game
Landing Page:

User Action: Selects a thematic scenario (e.g., Women In Tech).
Goal: Begin playing the trivia game.
Gameplay Page:

User Action: Answers trivia questions, progresses through levels.
Feedback: Receives immediate feedback on answers.
Goal: Reach level 20 and receive a certificate.
Completion Page:

User Action: Views and shares certificate (optional).
Goal: Achievement of completing the game.
3. Immersive Interactive Section
Selection Page:

User Action: Chooses difficulty level (e.g., Intermediate).
Goal: Start interactive video session.
Video Viewing Page:

User Action: Watches interactive video.
Interaction: Answers questions related to the video.
Feedback: Receives immediate feedback on answers.
Goal: Complete video session and earn rewards (badges, points).
Reward Page:

User Action: Views earned rewards and options to proceed.
Goal: Reflect on progress and consider further engagement.
4. DEI Resources Hub
Main Page:

User Action: Navigates to "Resources" section.
Goal: Explore curated links and information.
Resource Pages:

User Action: Clicks on a resource category (e.g., Articles).
Interaction: Views list of resources, filters by interest.
Goal: Find relevant DEI resources and engage with content.
Feedback Form:

User Action: Provides feedback or suggests new resources.
Goal: Contribute to platform improvement and community engagement.
